title: No doomsday asteroid today - Click Orlando
text:
NASA put out another statement this past week that asteroid 86666 was going to pass safely by Earth on Saturday, seeking to quell what had become doomsday panic among some. "It poses zero threat," the space agency's Near-Earth Object office tweeted, stating that the asteroid would miss our planet by 15 million miles.
